    "parsing_res_list": [
        {
            "block_label": "paragraph_title",
            "block_content": "#### 1.2. Problem statement ",
            "block_bbox": [
                213,
                197,
                488,
                220
            ],
            "block_id": 0,
            "block_order": 1
        },
        {
            "block_label": "text",
            "block_content": "In today's pseudo-digital landscape, any task related to documents is handled in two ways; analog or digital. Either the document is a piece of paper or it is made up of bits representing the symbols. Both of these ways have their own faults and benefits, but the main problem, in our view, lies in the separation of these two ways. For the world to truly enter a digital era and reap all the benefits gained from digitization, we must bridge the gap between the two aforementioned ways of handling documents.",
            "block_bbox": [
                210,
                283,
                1044,
                515
            ],
            "block_id": 1,
            "block_order": 2
        },
        {
            "block_label": "text",
            "block_content": "Though this sounds trivial, a document may contain various types of texts, images and tables. Managing various documents ranging from PDFs and Word files to scanned images is an everyday task for a lot of people. While these documents often contain important information, much of that content remains locked away in unsearchable formats, difficult and burdensome to comb through. Users frequently struggle to extract meaningful data from image-based files or poorly formatted documents,leading to inefficiencies, manual transcription, and loss of time.",
            "block_bbox": [
                211,
                572,
                1045,
                845
            ],
            "block_id": 2,
            "block_order": 3
        },
        {
            "block_label": "text",
            "block_content": "Traditional document editors typically only offer basic storage and retrieval capabilities, but they fall short when it comes to making document content truly accessible and actionable. They lack built-in OCR tools to convert images into editable text, cannot reliably preserve formatting during file conversions, and provide no intelligent way to query or interact with document content. This creates significant barriers, mainly for professionals who need to go through several documents every day.\n\n",
            "block_bbox": [
                210,
                901,
                1044,
                1172
            ],
            "block_id": 3,
            "block_order": 4
        },
        {
            "block_label": "paragraph_title",
            "block_content": "#### 1.3. Objectives ",
            "block_bbox": [
                214,
                1232,
                389,
                1259
            ],
            "block_id": 4,
            "block_order": 5
        },
        {
            "block_label": "text",
            "block_content": "The objective of our project is:",
            "block_bbox": [
                212,
                1319,
                512,
                1343
            ],
            "block_id": 5,
            "block_order": 6
        },
        {
            "block_label": "text",
            "block_content": "To develop an application to scan documents (both digital and handwritten)while preserving their format with a chatbot to answer any query related to the scanned document.\n\n",
            "block_bbox": [
                248,
                1401,
                1045,
                1506
            ],
